quality_annotation.video_description: In this video, an educator sits on a chair reading a book out loud. Another adult sits on the floor supporting the children. The educator reading out loud has to stop and ask a child to sit down. She continues reading and the toddlers are engaged, pointing at the pages and babbling/talking out loud. The children continue to move around as she reads but they remain engaged.
